==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Coupler
<hw>Coup"ler</hw> <pr>(k?p"l?r)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>One who
couples; that which couples, as a link, ring, or shackle, to connect
cars.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Coupler of an organ</b></col>, <cd>a contrivance by which
any two or more of the ranks of keys, or keys and pedals, are connected
so as to act together when the organ is played.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Couplet</ent>⟦br⟧
